					<gmd:title>
						<gco:CharacterString>UK Air Quality Reanalysis (AQREAN), 2003-2019</gco:CharacterString>
					</gmd:title>
					<gmd:date gco:nilReason="missing" />
					<gmd:presentationForm>
						<gmd:CI_PresentationFormCode codeList="http://www.isotc211.org/2005/resources/Codelist/gmxCodelists.xml#CI_PresentationFormCode" codeListValue="tableDigital" codeSpace="ISOTC211/19115">tableDigital</gmd:CI_PresentationFormCode>
					</gmd:presentationForm>
				</gmd:CI_Citation>
			</gmd:citation>
			<gmd:abstract>
				<gco:CharacterString>
					The AQREAN Surface Level Bias Corrected dataset provides a refined, observation-adjusted record of key air pollutants for the United Kingdom and Republic of Ireland. This version of the dataset is presented as annual mean datasets (consisting of one file per year for each case) spanning the period from 2003 to 2019. It is derived by applying a Statistical Post Processing of Observations (SPPO) method to the raw AQREAN reanalysis model output to correct biases using ground-based monitoring data from urban, suburban, and rural background sites within the Automatic Urban and Rural Network (AURN) and the Republic of Ireland network.

					Bias corrections are specifically applied to surface-level concentrations of O3, NO, NO2, SO2, CO, PM2.5, and PM10. While the underlying reanalysis is generated at an hourly temporal resolution, this specific dataset provides annual values at a 0.1-degree (~10 km) horizontal resolution in NetCDF format. Unlike the standard surface-level product, these files are land-masked, specifically excluding sea-based locations and Northern France, as observations for bias correction are only available for land-based locations in the UK and Ireland. Version 1.1 features an improved land-sea mask and includes calculated NOx concentrations derived from the corrected NO and NO2 levels.
					
					Full details about this dataset can be found at https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/bad1f0f37372421eb777e307b71a28cd
				</gco:CharacterString>
			</gmd:abstract>
			<gmd:purpose>
				<gco:CharacterString>Datasets generated by the Met Office to provide a representation of past pollutant concentrations across the UK.</gco:CharacterString>
			</gmd:purpose>
